____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== SET UP THE BASICS ===
    ☐ Learn how to use libc for system calls in Rust.
    ☐ Create a simple TCP server that listens for connections on a port and accepts incoming clients.
    ☐ Read raw HTTP requests and print them for debugging.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== PARSE HTTP REQUESTS ===
    ☐ Parse the HTTP request `line, headers, and body` into a struct.
    ☐ Print the parsed HTTP request for debugging.
    ☐ Understand how to extract the requested file path or action.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== SEND RESPONSES ===
    ☐ Create a simple HTTP response struct:
    ☐ Generate HTTP responses with headers (`Content-Type`, `Content-Length`, etc.) and a body.
    ☐ Send a simple HTTP response to the client.
    ☐ Understand how to send different types of responses.
    ☐ Handle basic files: serve static HTML, CSS, JS, or images.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== ADD I/O MULTIPLEXING ===
    ☐ Learn how to use `epoll` (or equivalent) to handle multiple clients efficiently.
    ☐ Implement I/O multiplexing in the server.
    ☐ Handle multiple clients concurrently.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== ADD ADVANCED FEATURES ===
    ☐ Implement:
        ☐ Support for GET, POST, and DELETE methods.
        ☐ File uploads.
        ☐ Session and cookie handling.
        ☐ Default error pages (400, 403, etc.).
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== HANDLE CONFIGURATION ===
    ☐ Add support for configuration files.
    ☐ Read server configuration from a file.
    ☐ Parse a configuration file to set server options (e.g., routes, limits).
    ☐ Allow users to specify the server's port, IP address, and other settings.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== ADD CGI SUPPORT ===
    ☐ Learn how to use CGI scripts to generate dynamic content.
    ☐ Implement CGI support in the server.
    ☐ Execute CGI scripts and return the output to the client.
    ☐ Understand how to pass environment variables to CGI scripts.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
=== STRESS TESTING ===
    ☐ Use `siege` to test and ensure your server doesn't crash under load.
